# FORE — environment variables (local dev — DO NOT COMMIT .env.local)

## Core (always)

```bash
# ML_MODE=inline  → run math inside Next.js (NO Render needed — recommended for Vercel-only deploy)
# ML_MODE=render  → call external Python service at RENDER_ML_BASE_URL
ML_MODE=inline
RENDER_ML_BASE_URL=
GROQ_API_KEY=
GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.1-8b-instant
GROQ_CRITIC_MODEL=llama-3.1-8b-instant
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000

# Public site URL used for OAuth redirect URIs
AUTH_REDIRECT_BASE=http://localhost:3000

# Optional Tier 2 APIs
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=
ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM
EXA_API_KEY=

# Optional multi-instance rate limiting (Upstash Redis REST)
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=
```

## Full-stack mode (JWT + PostgreSQL + OAuth)

```bash
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://fore:fore_dev_pass@localhost:5432/fore
JWT_ACCESS_SECRET=
DATA_ENCRYPTION_KEY=

# Google OAuth (https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials)
# Authorized redirect URI: {AUTH_REDIRECT_BASE}/api/auth/oauth/google/callback
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Microsoft Entra ID (Azure Portal → App registrations)
# Redirect URI: {AUTH_REDIRECT_BASE}/api/auth/oauth/microsoft/callback
MS_CLIENT_ID=
MS_CLIENT_SECRET=
MS_TENANT_ID=common
```

### Setup (beginner — creates `.env.local` for you)

```bash
git pull origin main
npm install
bash scripts/setup_local_env.sh
# paste your Neon DATABASE_URL when asked (or pass it as the first argument)
npx prisma generate
npx prisma db push
npm run dev
```

Then open http://localhost:3000/api/auth/providers  
Register with email, or fill Google/Microsoft keys in `.env.local` and restart.  
Without DATABASE_URL, use “Explore with demo data” on /login.  

**Never commit** `.env` or `.env.local` — they are gitignored.
